Data Structure: A node class represents the student structure, holding data fields (name, Aadhar, phone, marks, etc.) and a pointer node *link to the next node. 

Memory Management: Students are added dynamically to the heap (new node()), allowing the list to grow or shrink without predefined limits. The system uses delete to free memory during deletion.

Linked List Operations:
Add (Append): Traverses the list from the head (h) to find the last node (while (t->link != NULL)) and connects it to the new node (t->link = cn).
Search/Modify: Traverses the list comparing user-inputted roll numbers with node data.
Delete: Identifies the target node and updates the previous node's link to skip the deleted node (prev->link = t->link).
Input Handling: cin.ignore() is used to clear the input buffer, allowing getline() to read full names and addresses correctly. 

Workflow

Initialize: Head pointer h is initialized to NULL (empty list).
Menu Loop: A while(true) loop ensures the program runs continuously until the 'Exit' option is chosen.
Operations: A switch-case block processes the CRUD operations:
Case 1 (Add): Creates a new node at the end.
Case 2 (Search): Displays student details if found, or "not found".
Case 3 (Modify): Updates specific details of a student by ID.
Case 4 (Delete): Removes a student from the list, handling pointers to maintain structure.
Case 5 (Display): Iterates through the list to print all entries.
Case 6 (Exit): Terminates the program. 
